      • points

        public Iterable<Point> points()
        Array of point objects that represent points that are relevant to the type of shape. For example, for a triangle, points would include the x,y coordinates of the vertices of the recognized triangle. The points represent the coordinates of points used to create the perfectly drawn shape that is closest to the original input. They may not exactly match.
        Returns:
        Array of point objects
